• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Embattled Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane is to brief Parliament's Justice portfolio committee on her annual performance plan and budget on Tuesday. Her appearance comes after the same committee received a letter from Absa lawyers accusing Mkhwebane of lying to Parliament. Mkhwebane appeared before the committee on 6 March to explain details in her report into the apartheid-era bailout of Absa predecessor Bankorp. READ: Mkhwebane's Absa report set aside with costs The lawyers’ letter points out a number of instances in which the Public Protector misled Parliament.  eNCA